    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-01-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that the suggestion contained in Mr. Conger’s telegram of the 1st
                    instant had been under consideration here for some time. That, China having
                    yielded to joint demands, it is now timely to act upon the suggestion which it
                    is thought may already have been the occasion of a comparison of views among Mr.
                    Conger’s colleagues.</p>
                <p>The President’s proposal to transfer treaty and indemnity negotiations to
                    Washington or Europe has been communicated to the other powers by
                    telegraph.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
